Q2. Given a sorted array of integers, what can be the minimum worst-case time complexity to find ceiling of a number x in given array? The ceiling of an element x is the smallest element present in array which is greater than or equal to x. Ceiling is not present if x is greater than the maximum element present in array. For example, if the given array is {12, 67, 90, 100, 300, 399} and x = 95, then the output should be 100.
Ans -  O(log(n))
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
